# Beiza-Web ‚Äî Cursor rules

## PROTECTED COMPONENTS

### Heritage page hero
Canonical frame (`HERITAGE_HERO_DEFAULTS` / `src/data/heritage-hero-canonical.json`): posX 80, posY 100, scale 111, textSide right, overlayStrength 71, copyRaiseVh 0. Protect:
- Text block RIGHT aligned (default)
- Gradient flows left (dark on the right, light on the left)
- `beiza-elder-gye-nyame-hero.png` ‚Äî do not swap, do not crop
- Subject's face and Gye Nyame panel must always be visible
- "Plan your Heritage experience ‚Üí" scrolls to `#consultation`
- "Already lost someone? Recover a voice ‚Üí" links to `/recover`

### Tree canvas page (/circle/[id]/tree, /legacy/circle)
- Full screen layout (100vw √ó 100vh) ‚Äî never revert to page layout
- Header: 52px, fixed, minimal app bar
- Canvas: fills everything below header; no border, no rounded container
- No max-width containers anywhere on this route
- Fullscreen toggle must always be present on canvas controls

### Tree canvas nodes
- **`family_people` gender/career (read path):** `GET /api/circle/tree-data` does `SELECT *` on `family_people` ‚Äî `gender`, `career`, and any new columns arrive in `people[]` automatically. **No changes to that API route** for reads; wire UI/types from the payload only. Writes may still need `tree-person` or Supabase updates if editable.
- **Same-session prompts:** If gender/career UI is requested together with an earlier **alt+drag** (canvas pan) prompt in one Cursor session, alt+drag is already covered ‚Äî do not duplicate that work; only add gender/career display/edit from `people[]`.
- steven.oppong node with photo: DO NOT change the photo or layout
- Edge color: rgba(68,102,255,0.5) ‚Äî never white or gray
- Handle color: #E6A817
- Disconnect: right-click edge ‚Üí Remove connection, OR select edge + Backspace; right-click person node ‚Üí Disconnect node (removes all edges for that person)
- **Group nodes:** `layoutGroupNodes` normalises child coords to `(0,0)` inside the group bbox before setting `parentId`; children use `extent: "parent"`. Parent group nodes must appear before children in the nodes array. Keyboard `G` groups selection ‚Äî guard `isTypingInInput()` so typing in the edit popover does not trigger it. Save `canvas_x`/`canvas_y` as absolute positions (parent offset + child relative).
- **`onNodeDragStop`:** Read the current handler before editing. Preserve: `setPositionOverrides`, `setEdges` person-edge refresh via `treeEdgesToFlowEdges`, and `savePersonCanvasPosition`. Use `buildPersonAbsolutePositionMap` for edge refresh (not raw `node.position` when grouped). `useRef` must be imported from React for `groupStateRef`.

### Homepage hero (layout only)
- Full bleed (100vw) ‚Äî no max-width on the outer hero shell
- Nav: 100% width, padding 0 48px (`px-12`), no max-width wrapper
- Hero copy block: max-width 680px, left-aligned, `md:pl-20` ‚Äî do not change hero image asset or studio frame values
